nodes.body: If L30 till L90 are moved to a proper home in mathlib, then I think this is ready for merging.

It's not clear to me that `SmoothSupportedOn` should move to mathlib: it's really an ad hoc construction done just for the proof, not something of broader interest. On the other hand, ` Module.Finite R (restrictTotalDegree Ïƒ R N)` should definitely move to mathlib, but we couldn't find a good home for it. Maybe create a new file?

#find_home may produce false negatives if the statement (or the proof) pick up instances defined in more advanced files when more elementary instances suffice (reported [on Zulip](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Exterior.20algebras.20everywhere.2E.2E.2E/near/409942700)). Because of this I'm not really sure we need a new file.

This should be an easy PR but needs a new file because there's nothing that imports both MvPolynomial and AnalyticOn. I think the correct generality is that you can eval on a family of analytic functions `Ïƒ â†’ E â†’ F` for a NormedSpace `E` and a NormedAlgebra `F` over a NontriviallyNormedField R. If `E` is finite dimensional Hausdorff, any linear `E â†’ F` is continuous, so you can state the result with a linear map `E â†’â‚—[R] Ïƒ â†’ F`.

```suggestion
lemma analyticOn_eval {R Ïƒ : Type*} [Fintype Ïƒ] [IsROrC R] (P : MvPolynomial Ïƒ R) :
    AnalyticOn R (fun x â†¦ eval (EuclideanSpace.equiv Ïƒ R x) P) univ := fun x _ â†¦ by
  apply P.induction_on (fun r â†¦ ?_) (fun p q hp hq â†¦ ?_) fun p i hp â†¦ ?_ -- refine doesn't work
  Â· simp_rw [eval_C]; exact analyticAt_const
  Â· simp_rw [eval_add]; exact hp.add hq
  Â· simp_rw [eval_mul, eval_X]; exact hp.mul ((ContinuousLinearMap.proj (R := R) i).analyticAt x)
```
